c: 5
v: 52
t: "And yet thou canst see how those in whose hearts there is disease vie with one another for their good will, saying [to themselves], \"We fear lest fortune turn against us.\" But God may well bring about good fortune [for the believers] or any [other] event of His own devising, whereupon those [waverers] will be smitten with remorse for the thoughts which they had secretly harboured within themselves"